                            <comment id="17091526" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2020 12:46:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What version of Camel do you use? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17091531" author="pradeep.kalvakolu" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2020 12:47:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;3.1.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17091544" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2020 12:59:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks can you try with Camel 3.2.0 release &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17091548" author="pradeep.kalvakolu" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2020 13:03:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am having same issue with Camel 3.2.0 as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17091580" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2020 13:33:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That tool is a copy of the old swagger plugin that supports both json and yaml so I am actually not aware of whether we have yaml support in this too. But as yaml can be transformed to json then it should be doable. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17093489" author="pradeep.kalvakolu" created="Mon, 27 Apr 2020 13:07:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So is it possible to confirm if the yaml support exists with this plugin. If it doesn&apos;t exists, is it possible to include it, may be, in the next version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17094490" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 28 Apr 2020 13:20:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah I think it would be doable by adding the yaml parser that we have in swagger and use it in this module too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17094494" author="pradeep.kalvakolu" created="Tue, 28 Apr 2020 13:25:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok great. When can we expect this change, any idea?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17094557" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 28 Apr 2020 14:29:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay found out the issue and have it fixed for next release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
